MEET THE NEW STAFF:
Ms. Joetta Delay- JH Remote Learning Assistant
Most of the kids know me, Ms. Joetta. I have drove a bus at Paw Paw Schools for almost 20 years, both full time and as sub driver. I went back to school when I was 48 years young and received my Bachelors degree in Early Childhood. I then began my career in Substitute teaching. I have 4 ‚Äúgrown‚Äù (haha) children, twin boys, one is a paramedic in Rockford and the other is in the Army stationed currently in Georgia, my oldest daughter lives in Cincinnati and is a manger at Texas Roadhouse and my youngest daughter works as a CNA in Shabbona. I love working with children, spoiling the grandchildren, helping on the farm during harvest and planting seasons and the Chicago Cubs! My role at Paw Paw School this year will be to help teachers with remote learning students and any other needs plus drive bus! As I‚Äôve been told I‚Äôm the jack of all trades staff member this year! ü§£ I look forward to working with the great students of Paw Paw School.

post_text:
MEET THE NEW STAFF:
Mrs. Susan Stastny- K-4 Special Education
I returned back to school after my children started school and graduated from the University of Dubuque with a Bachelors of Science in Education. I received my Masters of Education in 2001 from National Louis University. I have taught all types of special education from elementary resource, cognitively impaired students and most recently high school resource in the science area. My goal is to provide children with learning issues the skill to master reading and math in their unique learning style and how to use resources that will help them succeed in life.
I have a blended family of 4 grown children and 9 grandchildren. I currently live in Nelson with my 18 year old granddaughter as she attends college to be a math teacher. I look forward to working at Paw Paw this year.

MEET OUR NEW STAFF:
Mrs. Janis Dunklau
Reading Specialist
I am a Paw Paw resident since 1990.
I have a Bachelor's degree in Elementary Education and a Masters Degree in Early Childhood. I have been an educator my whole adult career. I have worked in the western suburban schools before coming to Paw Paw and in Paw Paw School for many years as a substitute.
I love to teach. It is my calling.
I have two children that went to and graduated from PawPaw Schools
Both adults now who are living and working independently.
In my free time I love to be outdoors. You may see me walking or riding my bike. I also enjoy gardening as well as kayaking.

post_text:
Teacher Appreciation Week Continues:
Today we give a BIG shout out to our...
BUS DRIVERS- They are there to pick up the students through the rain and snow. They give high-fives and lots of smiles. We appreciate all they do to get our kids back and forth safely.
NURSE- She can be found in her office giving icepacks, bandaids and checking for injuries. She has a calming demeanor and students are always stopping by to say Hi when she is in the building. We sure do appreciate all that she does.
SOCIAL WORKERS/SPEECH- Our social workers work with individuals and groups to help with student issues and the school climate. Our Speech teacher helps students become better learners and communicators. So many students benefit from all of their services in our school.
TECHNOLOGY- Paw Paw is very fortunate to have Ipads and Chromebooks for all of our students. We have Smartboards in all of our classrooms. Our Tech director keeps us up and running.

text:
SPIRIT WEEK...

post_text:
Teacher Appreciation Week Continues:
Today we would like to give a BIG shout out to our...
OFFICE STAFF- They are our organizers, our front line, and the ones always answering our phones. They stay late and come in early. We would be lost with them.
CUSTODIANS- What a beautiful school we have, and it wouldn't be possible with the "team". They keep our building shining from top to bottom, inside and out.
LIBRARIAN- These are not your average book-nooks. Our librarys have a theme and always so well decorated. You can catch them reading to students and working with them on computer. They are a big part of our education team.
WE ARE FAMILY!

CUSTODIANS- What a beautiful school we have, and it wouldn't be possible with the "team". They keep our building shining from top to bottom, inside and out.
LIBRARIAN- These are not your average book-nooks. Our librarys have a theme and always so well decorated. You can catch them reading to students and working with them on computer. They are a big part of our education team.
WE ARE FAMILY!

We would like to share a free reading site that offers books in several languages. The site comes up in English but families can change the language of their choice by clicking on the pencil icon. The site is https://www.uniteforliteracy.com/

Once on the site, it is required to enter the country and the zip code of your residence. That's all. The site is easy to navigate. It offers books by categories. Kids can listen to the books and read along or they can read independently.

post_text:
Parents, Guardians and Staff:

Note: There will be no student attendance from March 16 through March 30, 2020.

Due to an increase in nearby counties with confirmed cases of COVID-19, the Paw Paw District will not hold school on Monday, March 16 as previously stated. This decision was made after the Governor‚Äôs Press Conference late afternoon today.

Teachers and Staff will be reporting on Monday, March 16, to prepare Alternative Education Plans for students. We will have more information on distribution of learning materials for you tomorrow.

We will hold the regular Board of Education meeting on Monday evening and are asking that everyone observe social distancing protocols as requested by the health departments.

As this health situation evolves, we may have to make changes to our decisions and protocols as needed.

Important Notice About JR. 10 Conference Activities
The Jr. 10 Conference continues to actively monitor reports on COVID-19 and follow guidance from the Illinois Department of Public Health and local health departments.

They has decided to postpone the Jr. 10 Spelling Bee at Serena High School scheduled for March 17, 2020. We are evaluating each Conference event as the situation continues to evolve.

All decisions are being made with the safety and well being of our students in mind, and we are being as responsive as possible with the information we are gathering.
